Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and text summarization. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as the paper deals with summarizing multiple documents, which is a common task in information retrieval. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses an unsupervised approach and a distributed bag of words model, which are machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with automated summarization, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses sentence selection and beam search algorithms to improve the performance of the model.
